description:
&lt;p&gt;Would you like the opportunity to develop your skills and knowledge as Clinical Lead in Physiotherapy. If so we have the opportunity for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity in Erewash for a highly motivated experienced Physiotherapist to support Integrated Community Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide support and supervision to the Integrated Community team, the Community Support and In-Patient beds, whilst supporting the therapy transformation into a core and rapid service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be actively involved in the promotion of high quality care and the development of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work alongside many other disciplines and MDT members, including an Clinical Lead for Occupational Therapy and District Nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This opportunity would suit an individual who would like to develop their leadership skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be able to demonstrate professional, well-established and effective communication and leadership skills to support the education and development of other physiotherapists, healthcare professionals and physiotherapy students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a DCHS employee it will be your responsibility to ensure that your behaviour and values reflect those set out in the DCHS Way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will involve working across different areas so access to a car and being able to drive is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fee Buswell-Marsh, ICM&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;fiona.buswell@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07580 311461&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;INFORMAL DISCUSSIONS WELCOMED.&lt;/p&gt;
